Summary

	This is a C++ implementation of the DCPU16 from Mojang's game 0x10c.
	It is based on the 1.7 specification (see doc directory).
	0x10c's website : http://0x10c.com/

Current features

	- DASM16 assembler
	- Hardware commands
	- Interrupts
	- LEM1802 emulation (only supports the default font and palette)
	- CPU state display with an overlay by hitting TAB
	- Auto textual memory dump before and after running

Planned features

	- More hardware devices
	- Debug tools / disassembler
	- IDE?

Compiling / dependencies
		
	SFML 1.6 : http://www.sfml-dev.org/index.php
	
	The project is compiled with GCC.
	
Releases

	Not available for now, I will upload Linux binaries soon.
	Windows binaries will come after for stable releases only.

How to use

	In the command line :
	
	dcpu yourFile	# will assemble yourFile and run it
	dcpu			# will assemble and run cputest.dasm (default, should print help later)


